<DocsLayout
  title="FAQ"
  description="Answers to common questions about using SignalPaper as an Astro author theme."
>
  <h2>What is SignalPaper?</h2>
  <p>SignalPaper is a content-first Astro theme for authors who want to publish writings, projects, tags, bilingual content, and searchable long-form pages.</p>

  <h2>Is SignalPaper a personal website or a theme?</h2>
  <p>This repository is prepared as a reusable theme. The included content is official demo content and should be replaced when you build your own site.</p>

  <h2>Does it require a backend?</h2>
  <p>No. SignalPaper builds to a static site. Search is generated at build time with Pagefind.</p>

  <h2>Can I disable bilingual publishing?</h2>
  <p>The default demo is bilingual. You can remove the second content tree and routes if you want a single-language site, but the first release is optimized for the included English and Chinese structure.</p>

  <h2>Are analytics, comments, and newsletters enabled by default?</h2>
  <p>No. These integrations are off by default so a fresh install does not send requests to third-party services.</p>
</DocsLayout>

